question: Which country houses "Calanques National Park"?
explanation: Calanques National Park is an IUCN Category II national park located in France, established in 2012. This national park houses the Massif des Calanques terrain. Several of the park's best-known features include the Calanque de Sormiou, Calanque de Morgiou, Calanque de Port-Miou, Calanque de Sugiton, and Cosquer Cave.
